  "tribunal": {
   "defense": "The available documentation does not provide an innocent business explanation (such as credit notes, correcting entries, FX/timing differences, or other mitigating business reasons) for the four same-day payments to Castor Papier GmbH, each just below the EUR 10,000 approval threshold. The payments are all labeled as 'Teilzahlung Lieferantenrechnung' (partial payment of supplier invoice) and share the same collective transaction reference (SAMMEL-200007), strongly suggesting they pertain to one liability. The payments are split over one day (with different times) and sum to EUR 39,040. No evidence of a prior correcting entry, credit note, foreign exchange impact, invoice dispute, or operational requirement for splitting the payments is cited in the provided records. The documented internal controls (see JET workpaper) explicitly flag this splitting pattern (K5) as indicative of possible threshold avoidance risk.",
   "defenseCitations": [
    {
     "docId": "begleitdokumente-pruefungsplanung-jet-2025",
     "ref": "l.1-15",
     "quote": "(K5) mehrere Teilzahlungen an einen Kreditor knapp unter der Freigabegrenze"
    }
   ],
   "verdict": "confirmed",
   "reasoning": "The defense concedes there is no documented innocent business explanation for the four payments, each just below the EUR 10,000 approval threshold and occurring on the same day to the same creditor, under a single reference. The cited internal control (K5) in the JET workpaper specifically flags such splitting as a risk for threshold avoidance. No evidence is provided of operational necessity, credit notes, foreign currency effects, or related mitigating factors. As all submitted evidence is consistent with the allegation and the defense is not supported by documentation, the allegation is confirmed."
  }
