  "tribunal": {
   "defense": "The documents confirm that MV-U05 both created the Ratio Consulting GmbH vendor and posted all related invoices and payments. There is no evidence of a credit note, correcting entries, or fulfillment of segregation of duties for this vendor. The payments and bookings all cite 'Beratungsleistungen lt. Rahmenvertrag,' suggesting legitimate business under a framework contract. However, the clear breach of the intended segregation of duties (as outlined in Berechtigungsauswertung_2025.xlsx and Pruefungsplanung_JET_2025.docx) is present, and no documentary evidence offers an innocent explanation for this (such as emergency override, explicit secondary approval, or different, missed logs). Therefore, based on the evidence, no strong innocent explanation exists.",
   "defenseCitations": [
    {
     "docId": "begleitdokumente-stammdatenaenderungen-2025",
     "ref": "Stammdatenaenderungen_2025!r.8",
     "quote": "12.05.2025;Kreditor;209101;Ratio Consulting GmbH;Neuanlage Kreditor;;angelegt inkl. Bankverbindung;MV-U05;MV-U05;Ja"
    },
    {
     "docId": "begleitdokumente-berechtigungsauswertung-2025",
     "ref": "Berechtigungen!r.7",
     "quote": "MV-U05 | Einkauf | X |  | X | X |  |  |  | "
    },
    {
     "docId": "begleitdokumente-pruefungsplanung-jet-2025",
     "ref": "l.1-15",
     "quote": "Funktionstrennung zwischen Kreditoren-Stammdaten, Buchung und Zahlungslauf ist vorgesehen (Berechtigungsauswertung_2025.xlsx)."
    }
   ],
   "verdict": "confirmed",
   "reasoning": "The allegation is that segregation of duties was bypassed in the creation of and payments to Ratio Consulting GmbH, as the same user (MV-U05) created the vendor, posted all invoices and payments, with no evidence of goods receipt or fulfillment to justify the payments. The defense acknowledges the same facts, provides no documentary evidence of controls, overrides, or mitigating circumstances, and all cited documents confirm both the risk and that relevant duties should have been segregated. There is no evidence of credit notes, secondary review, or other compensating controls. Therefore, the breach of segregation of duties is confirmed per the available evidence."
  }
